pg_rage_terminator, custom bgworker for PostgreSQL
=========================================

Background worker able to kill random connections based on a configurable
chance.

This worker can use the following parameter to decide the chance to kill a
random backend.
- pg_rage_terminator.chance, chance to kill a random backend. Valid values are 0
  to 100. Where 0 disables the "rage" process. 100 ensures every backend is
  killed.
- pg_rage_terminator.interval, defines how often pg_rage_terminator looks for
  queries to kill in seconds. Valid valid are 0s to 3600s.
Rage backend scan is done with a loop operation on pg_stat_activity.

This worker is compatible with PostgreSQL 9.3 and newer versions.
